messages.text: Me too! Won’t be long now. It’s almost dark.
You remember the place to meet?
Of course! The bay at Lea View.
I miss you more than a flower misses the sun when a cloud passes between them.
That’s poetry. U should write it in a song.
I am. It’s called Missing Eva.
I want 2 hear u sing it. I should leave now. B4 my dad gets here.
He can’t keep us apart. You belong in my life.
My dad’s home early. He’s locking all the doors & turning on the alarms.
Can you get out thru your window?
Why does he hate me so much?
Because ur family is not religious.
u have to be born into it
so, he doesn’t hate you - just your religion.
but I know your parents hate me.
Cause your folks let the kids play with real guns.
My parents would ground me for life if they caught me in your house -
just gotta wait till my folks go 2 sleep
I’ll wait however long it takes
finally out! I had to feed the dog some peanut butter to keep him quiet.
the roads r all flooded!! & now so’s my engine!
No! the cops are turning back all cars.
gonna try 2 hitch a ride out
can u get to a gas station?
hey, just flagged a truck. The trucker jump-started my car.
I’m gonna stop at CalZ’s pizza. Maybe the flood won't be so bad there, I hope -
Eva I’m using speech to text it’s all flooded here got to turn back where are you
racing against this ginormous tidal wave!
o my god I see it
Aaron… I need to tell you something
My dad is pissed at me
He caught me walking up the stairs
I told him I went out to help some friends who were caught in the flood
That just made him more upset.
He’s angry at me, but more angry at the government.
He thinks they made it flood on purpose.
That they engineered the flood as an excuse to create a natural disaster -
No BS - He’s putting bullets in all his guns now.
He thinks the End Times are here.
Well what is it? A gov’t conspiracy or End Times?
I know you think he’s a kook - but he’s still my dad.
Not as much as I’m mad at this stupid flood -
They want me to follow the rules - and take extra law classes.
They also want us to move.
My dad says that global warming will force us into either Canada or South America.
They’re ready to sell everything and just split.
I have to see you again.
i feel like we're in jail
And no trial - just a guilty verdict.
what if we called social services?
Eva, can you get one of your dad's guns?
Can you take one of his guns when he's not looking-
and hide it where he can't find it?
Click below to see what happens next...
